Considering the consistent reaction conditions in the preparation of xPHTSO (x = 1.8, 3.4, 4.3, and 7.0), we propose that the nucleation amount of the Pt precursor (H2PtCl6·6H2O) is closely related to the final particle size of Pt NPs, which is adjusted by the acid or base additives in the solvent reduction process, as shown in Fig. 1a. First, the dissociated PtCl62-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
